                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d679">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1616: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1"
                            type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-09T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 9, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 9—12:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s 68, March 2, 5 p.m. British Minister informed me today that he has
                    been instructed to acquiesce in postponement of Boxer Indemnity payments if and
                    when we and Italians so acquiesce. Italian Chargé d’Affaires states his
                    Government is still considering matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
